    "GRAG surpasses RAG and LLM baselines.",
    "Notably, GRAG significantly outperforms the finetuned LLM in all metrics across both datasets without fine-tuning the LLM.",
    "Fine-tuning offers only marginal performance gains when GRAG is employed, as evidenced by the limited improvement on the WebQSP dataset, with the Hit@1 metric increasing from 0.7236 to 0.7275.",
    "This suggests that GRAG is a more effective strategy for enhancing the graph reasoning capabilities of LLMs than mere fine-tuning.",
    "This can significantly reduce the cost of training LLMs for graph-related tasks."
